<DOC><DOCNO> AP890602-0112 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-06-02-89 1232EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-SouthKorea-Graft     06-02 0114</FIRST><SECOND>AM-South Korea-Graft,0116</SECOND><HEAD>Former Transport Minister Sentenced for Taking Bribes</HEAD><DATELINE>SEOUL, South Korea (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   The former transportation minister wassentenced Friday to five years in prison for taking $870,000 inbribes while in office, court officials said.   Judge Hong suk-che at the Seoul District Criminal Court alsoruled that Cha Kyu-hun must give up the money he received in 1987.Cha received the money in exchange for authorizing a local businessto build a golf course.   The prosecution had demanded 10 years in prison and theforfeiture of the money.   Cha, 60, was arrested in December.   Two other businessmen, who allegedly acted as intermediaries inthe bribery scandal, were given suspended sentences.</TEXT></DOC>